assessment_title:

CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement:
CAdES is included in 2 national catalogues of recommended specifications. They belong to the Netherlands, and Spain. The National Interoperability Framework (NIF) of these Member States is fully aligned with at least 4 out of 5 sections of the European Interoperability Framework (EIF) according to the National Interoperability Framework Observatory (NIFO) factsheets.
See:
https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/collection/national-interoperability-framework-observatory-nifo/nifo-factsheets

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement:
ETSI’s standards-making process has been clearly defined after years of experience. The organisation has adopted the open approach which means direct participation and consensus as a basis to develop standards. All the stakeholders have the opportunity to participate directly in the process of standardisation through the technical committees created to develop ETSI’s technical specifications and standards. The decision-making process includes a public review, where stakeholders involved can provide technical feedback in order to enhance and maximize the quality and accuracy of the standards. 
See: 
https://www.etsi.org/standards/standards-making

assessment_title:

CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: The last version of the specification was launched in 2013 by the European Telecommunications Standards Institute. The fact of being a European Standard maintained and promoted by ETSI, provides value on its maturity and market acceptance to be used in the development of products.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: CAdES Baseline profile is being used in the context of the European internal market to ensure interoperability across borders when AdES signatures are required. Hence, it can be considered as an element fostering the creation of innovative solutions fostering the implementation of Once-only Principle along with other capabilities enhancing the relationship between public administrations and stakeholders.

assessment_title:

CAdES Baseline Profile

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: CAdES is business agnostic and in consequence, its Baseline Profile can be considered business agnostic as well. CAdEs Baseline profile is an extension to provide interoperability when AdES signatures need to be interchanged across borders in the context of the EU internal market. Thus, it can be used in any business domain requiring interoperability features along with eSignature.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: CAdES Baseline profile is an independent standard that can be implemented without dependencies on other technologies or platforms. Therefore, the specification can be implemented without hampering the interoperability but avoiding vendor lock-in.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: By providing necessary compliance requirements for the implementation of AdES signatures in the context of the European internal market, the selection and implementation of CAdES Baseline Profile does not hamper the interoperability of systems. In fact, it has been developed to ensure the interchange of digital documentation on electronic procedures and communications across borders.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: The implementation of the specification fosters the data portability according to its purpose. CAdES Baseline profile has been developed to provide basic features necessary for electronic procedures including eSignature across borders. The implementation of CAdES Baseline Profile enhances the interoperability in the context of the European Single Digital Market.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: By ensuring the availability of eSignatures elements and metadata, the specification avoids the users to provide information more than one time. Therefore, CAdES fosters the implementation of the Once-only Principle.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: The purpose of the specification is not related to e-accessibility. Therefore, this criterion is not applicable to this specification.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: By providing conformance levels and requirements in order to maintain eSignatures in the context of AdES signatures, it ensures and fosters the trustworthy data exchange between administrations and their stakeholders.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: The purpose of the specification is not related to the delivery of multilingual services. Therefore, this criterion is not applicable to this specification.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: By allowing the digital document exchange including eSignatures, the CAdES Baseline profile avoids the non-digital data exchange. This fact is a key point in the reduction of administrative burden.

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: Regarding eSignatures, CAdES includes features to the long-term preservation of data included in electronic signatures. The LTA-Level of requirements is covering the preservation, integrity of attributes and validation materials for the eSignatures ensuring the long-term accessibility. However, the specification is not strictly related to the functions of eArchiving.

assessment_title:

CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement: After carrying out information retrieval, no document or study has been found assessing the CAdES Baseline profile in terms of efficiency or effectiveness.

assessment_title:

CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement:
CAdES Baseline Profile is already associated with EIRA ABBs in the European Library Of Specifications (ELIS). Specifically, CAdES Baseline Profile can define the interoperability aspects of “e-Seal Creation Service”, “e-Seal Verification and Validation Service”, “e-Signature Creation Service”, and “e-signature Verification and Validation Service” ABBs of the EIRA Technical View.
See: 
https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/solution/elis/distribution/eliscataloguev100betaxlsx

See:
https://signatures-conformance-checker.etsi.org/pub/CAdESConformanceTestChecker_v1.0.pdf https://signatures-conformance-checker.etsi.org/pub/index.shtml

CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement:
CAdES has been included within the European Public Service “Digital Signature Service” (hereby DDS). The initiative includes three main features: the digital signature, the extension a digital signature, and the validation. Moreover, it is worth to note that DSS initiative included in the Connecting Europe Facility Programme context which aims to fund projects and initiatives for enhancing European public services. 

See:
https://ec.europa.eu/cefdigital/DSS/webapp-demo/doc/dss-documentation.html
https://ec.europa.eu/inea/connecting-europe-facility/cef-telecom

assessment_title:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
P1:
Electronic Signatures and Infrastructures (ESI);
CAdES Baseline Profile
statement:
No regulation has been found directly mentioning CAdES as a subject of the agreement. Despite this, eiDAS regulation is focused on electronic identification and trust services for electronic transactions. CAdES Baseline profile is specifying the profile of CMS signed-data on the context of the European Internal Market. Moreover, it is compliant with eiDAS regulation, a key enabler on the trustworthy data exchange across borders. 
See:
https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=uriserv%3AOJ.L_.2014.257.01.0073.01.ENG https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=celex%3A32006L0123
